title: "A cardinality envelope for the condensed classifying anima of spectral infinity-topoi: a synthesis across geometric, model-theoretic and set-theoretic instances"
version: "v1-preprint"
date-released: "2026-05-01"
authors:
  - family-names: "Vera Gómez"
    given-names: "Francisco Javier"
    affiliation: "Independent researcher"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0001-3516-5871"
abstract: >-
  Synthesis preprint formulating a candidate cardinality envelope for the underlying
  group at section level of the fundamental group of the condensed classifying anima of
  a spectral infinity-topos. The envelope 2^kappa, where kappa is the cardinality of
  the underlying point set, is shown consistent with seven attestations across three
  nominally unrelated mathematical branches (geometric, model-theoretic, set-theoretic)
  under the unifying classifying-anima construction recently announced by Haine.
  Falsifiable conjecture with explicit confidence levels per claim and an honest
  declaration of author position and LLM-assisted production method.
keywords:
